questions.title: How to get around in Vienna?
questions.answer: In Vienna you can use it for only ‚Ç¨7,60 for 24 hours. This includes the metro, tram, bus and S-Bahn. The app 'Quando' easily guides you through the city. For more options you can use Uber or Taxi

questions.title: How to get to the event location, Studio 44?
questions.answer: Studio 44 is situated at Rennweg 44. The closest stop to the address is the station Rennweg. You can reach it with trams O or 71, the bus line 77A or the S-Bahn (lines S1, S2, S3, S4 and S7).

questions.title: How to get to the afterparty?
questions.answer: The location of the afterparty is the Red Room. Its address is Stubenring 20 and you can reach it via the metro U3 Stubentor, tram 2 or bus lines 3A and 74A.

questions.title: How to print #CBC16 photos?
questions.answer: Every photo you upload to instagram or twitter with #CBC16 will be printed directly from the #tagg-it printer in the lobby. You can also send the picture to the chatbot via messenger. Give it a try!

questions.title: Where can I eat?
questions.answer: You can grab something to eat from Hy-kitchen inside the venue. They have awesome burgers! There are also the supermarkets Billa and Spar right across the street.

questions.title: Where can I get a t-shirt?
questions.answer: Unfortunately, t-shirts are only for volunteers, but we have awesome stickers and bags that you can get
